The paper deals with the computational complexity of finding backbones of boolean formulas, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves the study of sets of boolean formulas, which can be seen as a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the difficulty of producing backbones, which can be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography (cs.CR).
